---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Florida Tree Care Tools | ProTreeTrim"
  description="Free Florida tree care tools for homeowners comparing storm risk, problem trees, permit questions, emergency tree issues, and tree service options."
>
  <section class="tools-hero">
    <div>
      <p>Florida homeowner resource center</p>
      <h1>Florida Tree Care Tools</h1>
      <span>
        Use these homeowner-friendly tools before requesting a quote, comparing
        tree service options, checking a risky tree, or deciding whether a
        Florida tree issue needs monitoring, documentation, or urgent local help.
      </span>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/tools/emergency-tree-safety-checklist/">Open Emergency Checklist</a>
        <a href="/tools/florida-tree-care-advisor/">Open Tree Care Advisor</a>
        <a href="/tools/florida-problem-tree-guide/">View Problem Tree Guide</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tools-intro">
    <div class="intro-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Choose the right starting point</p>
      <h2>Not every tree question should start with removal</h2>
      <p>
        Florida properties can involve storm exposure, palms, mature oaks,
        roots near hardscape, HOA expectations, protected areas, and access
        issues. These tools help organize the first questions before a homeowner
        calls dispatch, reads a deeper guide, or compares local service options.
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="notice-card">
      <strong>Homeowner education only.</strong>
      <p>
        These tools do not diagnose trees, replace local permit review, or
        confirm protected-species status. For cracked, leaning, uprooted, or
        storm-damaged trees, keep people away from the hazard area and contact a
        qualified local provider.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="tools-grid-section" aria-label="Florida tree care tools">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p>Available tools</p>
      <h2>Start with a practical Florida tree care tool</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="tools-grid">
      <a class="tool-card primary" href="/tools/florida-tree-care-advisor/">
        <span class="card-kicker">Decision helper</span>
        <h3>Florida Tree Care Advisor</h3>
        <p>
          Get Florida-specific guidance based on your area, season, and property
          concern, then move to the most relevant guide or service page.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Storm risk and leaning trees</li>
          <li>Palm care, roots, stumps, and permits</li>
          <li>Region-aware homeowner guidance</li>
        </ul>
        <strong>Open advisor →</strong>
      </a>

      <a class="tool-card" href="/tools/florida-problem-tree-guide/">
        <span class="card-kicker">Problem trees</span>
        <h3>Florida Problem Tree Guide</h3>
        <p>
          Check common invasive, storm-prone, messy, high-maintenance, or
          hardscape-conflict trees before planning work near a home.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Brazilian pepper, melaleuca, ficus, and more</li>
          <li>Watch-for clues and homeowner next steps</li>
          <li>Service planning and related guides</li>
        </ul>
        <strong>Open guide →</strong>
      </a>

      <a class="tool-card emergency-card" href="/tools/emergency-tree-safety-checklist/">
        <span class="card-kicker">Emergency checklist</span>
        <h3>Emergency Tree Safety Checklist</h3>
        <p>
          Check whether a storm-damaged, leaning, cracked, blocked-access, or
          utility-adjacent tree issue should be treated as emergency, priority,
          or monitor-and-plan.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Roof, driveway, fence, and pool cage hazards</li>
          <li>Power-line and access-warning reminders</li>
          <li>Emergency, priority, or monitor guidance</li>
        </ul>
        <strong>Open checklist →</strong>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="planning-section" aria-label="Related tree care planning paths">
    <div class="planning-card dark county-card">
      <p>County planning</p>
      <h2>Permit and risk notes by Florida county</h2>
      <span>
        County hub pages now include safer permit and risk documentation notes,
        including reminders to verify city, HOA, protected-tree, mangrove,
        wetland, easement, and utility constraints before non-emergency work.
      </span>
      <div class="county-link-grid" aria-label="Featured Florida county hubs">
        <a href="/county/volusia/">Volusia County →</a>
        <a href="/county/broward/">Broward County →</a>
        <a href="/county/palm-beach/">Palm Beach County →</a>
        <a href="/county/miami-dade/">Miami-Dade County →</a>
        <a href="/county/orange/">Orange County →</a>
        <a href="/county/walton/">Walton County →</a>
        <a href="/county/hillsborough/">Hillsborough County →</a>
        <a href="/county/pinellas/">Pinellas County →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="planning-card">
      <p>Emergency planning</p>
      <h2>Know when not to wait</h2>
      <span>
        If a tree is cracked, leaning, uprooted, blocking access, resting on a
        structure, or near utility lines, do not stand beneath it. Keep people
        away and request local guidance.
      </span>
      <a href="/tools/emergency-tree-safety-checklist/">Open emergency checklist →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="quick-check-section">
    <div class="quick-check">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Before you call</p>
        <h2>Information that helps a provider understand the situation faster</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="check-grid">
        <div>
          <strong>Tree location</strong>
          <span>Front yard, side yard, backyard, near road, near structure, or near utility area.</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Visible risk</strong>
          <span>Cracks, leaning, uprooting, broken limbs, fungal growth, or recent storm damage.</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Access limits</strong>
          <span>Gates, fences, pools, pavers, pool cages, tight side yards, or soft soil.</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Documentation</strong>
          <span>Photos from a safe distance, insurance needs, HOA notes, or local permit questions.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .tools-hero {
    background: radial-gradient(circle at center, #164b34 0%, #082d20 72%);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: clamp(5rem, 10vw, 8rem) 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 6px solid #f25a06;
  }

  .tools-hero > div {
    max-width: 980px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .tools-hero p,
  .eyebrow,
  .section-heading p,
  .planning-card p,
  .card-kicker {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: #ffb703;
    font-weight: 900;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }

  .tools-hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5.8vw, 4.1rem);
    line-height: var(--heading-line-height);
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .tools-hero span {
    display: block;
    max-width: 820px;
    margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
    color: #bbf7d0;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .hero-actions a,
  .planning-card a {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-height: 3.3rem;
    max-width: 100%;
    padding: 0 1.4rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #f25a06;
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 900;
    text-decoration: none;
    box-shadow: 0 16px 35px rgba(242, 90, 6, 0.24);
  }

  .hero-actions a:nth-child(2),
  .planning-card:not(.dark) a {
    background: #e8fff1;
    color: #0f3f2a;
    border: 1px solid #b7f7ca;
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  .tools-intro,
  .planning-section,
  .quick-check-section {
    max-width: 1160px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(4rem, 7vw, 6rem) 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .tools-intro {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.3fr) minmax(300px, 0.7fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .intro-copy h2,
  .section-heading h2,
  .planning-card h2,
  .quick-check h2 {
    margin: 0;
    color: #0f3f2a;
    font-size: clamp(1.65rem, 3.2vw, 2.35rem);
    line-height: var(--heading-line-height);
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .intro-copy > p:last-child,
  .notice-card p,
  .planning-card span,
  .quick-check span {
    display: block;
    color: #475569;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .notice-card {
    background: #fff7ed;
    border: 1px solid #fdba74;
    color: #9a3412;
    border-radius: 1.5rem;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .notice-card strong {
    display: block;
    color: #9a3412;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .notice-card p {
    color: #9a3412;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tools-grid-section {
    background: #f8faf9;
    margin-top: clamp(4rem, 7vw, 6rem);
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .section-heading {
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }

  .section-heading p,
  .card-kicker,
  .planning-card p,
  .eyebrow {
    color: #f25a06;
  }

  .tools-grid {
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .tool-card {
    display: block;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #dbe4df;
    border-radius: 2rem;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: #475569;
    box-shadow: 0 18px 50px rgba(15, 63, 42, 0.08);
    min-height: 440px;
    min-width: 0;
    transition: transform 180ms ease, box-shadow 180ms ease;
  }

  .tool-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(15, 63, 42, 0.12);
  }

  .tool-card.primary {
    background: #082d20;
    color: #d1fae5;
  }

  .tool-card.primary .card-kicker { color: #ffb703; }

  .tool-card h3 {
    color: #0f3f2a;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 2.5vw, 2.05rem);
    line-height: var(--heading-line-height);
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .tool-card.primary h3 { color: #fff; }

  .tool-card p:not(.card-kicker) {
    line-height: 1.75;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .tool-card ul {
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .tool-card strong {
    color: #f25a06;
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .planning-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .planning-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #dbe4df;
    border-radius: 2rem;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    min-width: 0;
    box-shadow: 0 18px 50px rgba(15, 63, 42, 0.06);
  }

  .planning-card.dark {
    background: #082d20;
  }

  .planning-card.dark h2,
  .planning-card.dark span { color: #fff; }

  .planning-card > a {
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
  }

  .county-link-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 0.55rem;
    margin-top: 1.45rem;
  }

  .county-link-grid a {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    min-height: 2.45rem;
    padding: 0.58rem 0.78rem;
    border-radius: 0.78rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(187, 247, 208, 0.26);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.055);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    font-weight: 900;
    text-decoration: none;
    box-shadow: none;
    transition: background 180ms ease, border-color 180ms ease, transform 180ms ease;
  }

  .county-link-grid a:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    border-color: rgba(187, 247, 208, 0.48);
  }

  .quick-check-section {
    padding-bottom: 7rem;
  }

  .quick-check {
    background: #f8faf9;
    border: 1px solid #dbe4df;
    border-radius: 2rem;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .check-grid {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .check-grid > div {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #dbe4df;
    border-radius: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .check-grid strong {
    display: block;
    color: #0f3f2a;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .check-grid span {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-top: 0.55rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1050px) {
    .tools-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .tools-intro,
    .planning-section,
    .check-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .tool-card {
      min-height: 0;
    }

    .county-link-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .tools-hero h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 11vw, 3rem);
    }
  }
</style>
